ring and info searching through search engine.", "methods": {"run": {"type": "async_function", "description": "Answer a query by leveraging web search results. ", "signature": "(self, query: \'str\', rewrite_query: \'bool\' = True) -> \'str\'", "parameters": "Args: query (str): The original user query. rewrite_query (bool): Whether to rewrite the query for better web search results. Defaults to True. Returns: str: A detailed answer based on web search results. Raises: ValueError: If the query is invalid."}}, "tool_path": "metagpt/actions/search_enhanced_qa.py"}, "Engineer2": {"type": "class", "description": "A role who can think and act dynamically", "methods": {"write_new_code": {"type": "async_function", "description": "Write a new code file. ", "signature": "(self, path: \'str\', file_description: \'str\' = \'\') -> \'str\'", "parameters": "Args: path (str): The absolute path of the file to be created. file_description (optional, str): \\"Brief description and important notes of the file content, must be very concise and can be empty. Defaults to \\"\\"."}}, "tool_path": "metagpt/roles/di/engineer2.py"}, "CodeReview": {"type": "class", "description": "Review and fix the patch content from the pull request URL or a file.", "methods": {"fix": {"type": "async_function", "description": "Fix the patch content based on code review comments. ", "signature": "(self, patch_path: str, cr_file: str, output_dir: str) -> str", "parameters": "Args: patch_path: The local path of the patch file or the url of the pull request. cr_file: File path where code review comments are stored. output_dir: File path where code review comments are stored."}, "review": {"type": "async_function", "description": "Review a PR and save code review comments. Notes: If the user does not specify an output path, saved it using a relative path in the current working directory. ", "signature": "(self, patch_path: str, output_file: str, point_file: Optional[str] = None) -> str", "parameters": "Args: pat